The Ballon d'Or for 2015 was won by Lionel Messi. This was the fifth time that Messi had won the award, having previously won it in 2009, 2010, 2011, and 2012. In 2015, Messi had a highly successful season with Barcelona, winning La Liga, the Copa del Rey, and the UEFA Champions League. He scored a total of 52 goals and provided 26 assists in 61 appearances for the club that season.